p
p \mid 2^{p-1} -1
p \mid \binom{p}{k}
1 \le k \le p-1
\begin{align} 2^{p-1} u_p  &= -2^{p-1} + \frac12\bigg[ (1 + \sqrt{5})^p + (1-\sqrt{5})^p \bigg]\\ &= -2^{p-1} + \sum_{k=0, k\text{ even}}^p \binom{p}{k} \sqrt{5}^k\\ &= - ( 2^{p-1} - 1 ) + \sum_{\ell=1}^{\lfloor p/2\rfloor} \binom{p}{2\ell} 5^\ell \tag{*1} \end{align}
p \mid \text{RHS(*1)}\quad\implies\quad p \mid 2^{p-1} u_p\quad\implies\quad p \mid u_p
